events.name: Oklahoma Sooners at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Kyler Murray threw three touchdown passes and ran for another score and No. 6 Oklahoma scored two defensive TDs as the Sooners beat No. 12 West Virginia 59-56 Friday night to earn a spot in next week's Big 12 championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Slugfest: No. 6 Oklahoma outlasts No. 12 WVU 59-56

video.headline: Oklahoma outlasts West Virginia in offensive thriller

events.name: Washington Huskies at Washington State Cougars

headlines.description: Myles Gaskin broke free for an 80-yard touchdown run early in the fourth quarter, and No. 16 Washington won its second Pac-12 North Division title in three years, beating No. 7 Washington State 28-15 on a snowy Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Snow Dawgs: No. 16 Washington topples No. 7 Wazzu 28-15

events.name: UCF Knights at South Florida Bulls

headlines.description: No. 8 UCF lost quarterback McKenzie Milton to injury but still trounced South Florida 38-10 on Friday to extend the nation's longest winning streak to 24 games and complete a second consecutive undefeated regular season.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 8 UCF remains unbeaten, but loses QB Milton in 38-10 win

video.headline: McCrae runs free to complete hat trick

headlines.description: Sam Ehlinger threw for two touchdowns and ran for a score, and No. 11 Texas held off Kansas 24-17 on Friday to clinch a spot in the Big 12 title game.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 11 Texas beats Kansas 24-17, heads to Big 12 title game

video.headline: Texas' Ehlinger muscles in for 3-yard TD

headlines.description: Miguel Recinos drilled a 41-yard field goal through a driving rain as time expired and Iowa beat Nebraska 31-28 on Friday despite blowing a 15-point lead.
headlines.shortLinkText: Recinos' FG lifts Iowa over Nebraska 31-28 at final whistle

headlines.description: Junior Darrell Henderson rushed for 178 yards and two touchdowns -- setting a conference rushing record -- and Memphis rallied past Houston 52-31 on Friday to set up a rematch of last season's American Athletic Conference championship game with No. 8...
headlines.shortLinkText: Memphis wins, will face UCF in AAC title rematch

headlines.description: A.J. Ouellette ran for 169 yards and two touchdowns and Papi White became Ohio's all-time leader in yards receiving as the Bobcats rolled to a 49-28 victory over Akron on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ouellette, White lead Ohio past Akron 49-28

events.name: Buffalo Bulls at Bowling Green Falcons

headlines.description: Tyree Jackson threw a touchdown pass and Buffalo ran in four scores to beat Bowling Green 44-14 on Friday to claim its second straight Mid-American Conference East Division championship.
headlines.shortLinkText: Buffalo claims MAC East title, runs over Bowling Green 44-14

video.headline: Williams recovers fumble, returns it 69 yards for TD

events.name: Central Michigan Chippewas at Toledo Rockets

headlines.description: Freshman Bryant Koback rushed for 124 yards and two touchdowns, helping Toledo beat Central Michigan 51-13 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Toledo reaches 50 points again, beats Central Michigan

events.name: Eastern Michigan Eagles at Kent State Golden Flashes

headlines.description: Senior Ian Eriksen rushed for 118 yards and three touchdowns to power Eastern Michigan to a 28-20 victory over Kent State on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Eriksen carries Eastern Michigan past Kent State 28-20

headlines.description: In his final home game, Missouri quarterback Drew Lock rushed for two touchdowns and threw for two more as the Tigers beat Arkansas 38-0 on a damp and dreary Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lock leads Missouri in rout of Arkansas

events.name: Coastal Carolina Chanticleers at South Alabama Jaguars

headlines.description: Tra Minter ran for a career-high 203 yards and Cole Garvin and Evan Orth each threw a long touchdown pass to Jamarius Way to help South Alabama hold off Coastal Carolina 31-28 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Minter leads South Alabama past Coastal Carolina 31-28

video.headline: South Alabama WR Way catches 3rd TD pass

events.name: Virginia Cavaliers at Virginia Tech Hokies

headlines.description: Brian Johnson kicked a 42-yard field goal in overtime and Virginia Tech pulled out the wildest victory in its 100 meetings with Virginia, 34-31 on Friday night. The Hokies won their 15th in a row in the series and kept alive their hopes for a 26th...
headlines.shortLinkText: Overtime FG gives Hokies wild 34-31 win over Virginia

video.headline: Virginia Tech wins on forced fumble in OT

events.name: East Carolina Pirates at Cincinnati Bearcats

headlines.description: Redshirt freshman Desmond Ridder threw a career-high four touchdown passes in the first half, and Cincinnati wrapped up the regular season with 10 victories for the first time since 2012, routing East Carolina 56-6 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ridder throws 4 TDs as Cincinnati routs East Carolina 56-6

events.name: Oregon Ducks at Oregon State Beavers

headlines.description: CJ Verdell ran for 187 yards and four touchdowns, and also caught a scoring pass as Oregon defeated Oregon State 55-15 Friday in a Civil War victory that was marred by quarterback Justin Herbert's first-half injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: Verdell has 5 TDs in Oregon's 55-15 win over Oregon State
